The Dutch husband of Shamima Begum, who joined the Islamic State group in Syria in 2015 aged 15, has said he wants her to return to the Netherlands with him. Yago Riedijk and Ms Begum married days after she arrived inside IS territory. He admitted fighting for the group but says he now wants to return home with his wife and their newborn son. Mr Riedijk, 27, being held in a Kurdish detention centre in Syria,    faces a six-year jail term for joining a terror organisation if he returns to the Netherlands.  United States: Trump: IS woman barred from US return UK: IS teenager Shamima Begum 'gives birth' For Nigerian illegal aliens in the  Netherlands, it is a tough and risky life